---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { LINKEDIN_URL } from '../consts';
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Riddam Jain — staff engineer in Amsterdam, writing about cloud and application architecture, AI, books, and leading engineers."
>
  <h1>Hi, I'm Riddam 👋</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    I'm a staff engineer at Coolblue, based in Amsterdam. Over the last ten years —
    across media and e-commerce — I've spent most of my time on cloud and
    application architecture: designing systems that hold up in production, and
    helping the engineers around me do the same.
  </p>

  <p>
    A lot of my work these days lives where <strong>cloud architecture and AI</strong>
    meet — building on GCP and AWS, shaping data and ML pipelines, and figuring out
    how to make AI genuinely useful in production rather than just impressive in a
    demo. I care most about the parts that don't make the highlight reel:
    reliability, security, cost, and code the next person can actually maintain.
  </p>

  <p>
    A big part of the staff role is multiplying other people — mentoring, setting
    technical direction, and writing things down so a lesson only has to be learned
    once. This blog is part of that. It's where I share what I've learned, and
    honestly, where I figure out what I actually think. A few threads run through it:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="/engineering/"><strong>Engineering</strong></a> — deep dives and
      write-ups from real work: cloud and application architecture, AI-assisted
      development, tooling, and hard-won lessons.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/book-notes/"><strong>Book Notes</strong></a> — takeaways from books
      worth remembering, in my own words.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/leadership/"><strong>Leadership</strong></a> — on leading teams,
      growing engineers, and doing the work well.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/guides/"><strong>Playbooks</strong></a> — in-depth references and
      blueprints I've built for certifications, architecture, and core topics.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    If any of this resonates — or if you just want to disagree with me about
    something — I'd love to hear from you.
  </p>

  <p class="connect">
    <a href={LINKEDIN_URL}>Connect with me on LinkedIn →</a>
  </p>
</Base>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .connect {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
